deck_excerpt: This is the best Watt deck i could come up with. Its not a meta deck obviously but you can beat higher tier decks with this build sometimes.
deck_description: Basic protect the castle strategy. There isn't much to it attack directly every turn then try to cowboy for game if possible. Watt monsters attack directly over the course of the game and you protect them with your back row. You can also stun your opponent with fossil dyna. Power of the guardian is an interesting tech card i found. It helps to build up your watts attack over the course of the game while also protecting it from being destroyed by card effects and attacks. If left out for more than a few turns it can turn your watt monster into a 2k beat stick that can attack directly while having built in protection. This is one of the only decks i think Magic Cylinder is actually a viable choice over more protection like another mirror card. Mainly because the main strategy is to protect your watts while still doing enough damage each turn to win, Magic cylinder does both.

Feel free to change or side and Feedback is always welcomed :)

deck_description:
Code Talker, Backup, and Firewall ''Code Talker''

Appearance

The "Code Talkers" resemble warrior-like cybernetic humanoids whose armor is colored after their corresponding Attribute. They also each wield a different weapon to use in battle. Their bodies underneath the armor appear similar to the Ignis, especially Ai and Flame with their black designs.

Etymology

The archetype's name is derived from code talkers; individuals (typically Native American) who were used by the United States during wars in the 20th century as a means of encrypting and decrypting communications by using obscure languages that were not widespread, and were difficult to translate.

"Backup" monsters are themed after cybernetic employees.

''Firewall''

Appearance

Each member resembles a dragon-like cybernetic being.

Etymology

The series is named after a firewall in computing.   I add a card in this Deck Scrap-Iron Scarecrow

deck_excerpt: Zombie Control 2.0 with tiny danger added
deck_description: Uploaded a deck before, but thinking how to implement danger.  Thinking about current meta decks (Thunder Dragon, Sky striker, Trickstar, Salamangreat, Orcust, Pendulum)  The deck run still around control using hand trap.  Zombie + rivalry floodgate is still very annoying for most meta decks.  Only issue, the deck lacks of board protection. You can try to take out starving vernom or dragonecro of a number 23 witch has negates effect for everysingle card or number 22.  The deck is more a going first deck.  If win the first game, for the second game, side to go second.  Suggest to side out  1 doomking,  1 glow-up,  3 rivalry (since going second, we mainly focus on breaking the board instead for floodgate. But can keep it against trickstar since trickstar is a slower deck witch builds a less floodgate board)  3 mothman(same reason than before. Mothman is in the deck for putting cards in the gv and special summon.)  1 vampire fraulein(even to 2 since it's really a brick if you go second. Against most of the meta deck, it will take a lot of ressources to break the board)  So side out around 9 cards  side in  3 evenly (mostly against thunderdragon, salamangreat, orcust, )  3 ghost reaper (hurt a lot of the current meta deck witch demands a lot of the extra deck)  2 super poly  *if going against sky striker (no need to think too much, 2 anti-spell, imperial order and twin twister. Even you go second, having anti-spell can slow your opponent down a bit. with kagari limited, sky striker is already slower than before)  1 or 2 pankratops.

deck_description: cyber dragon + abc

This deck is all about destruction. You use the Metalfoes in the pendulum zone to destroy the Yang Zing monsters, giving you a set card and the Yang Zing special summons another Yang Zing from the deck. This lets you get monsters on the field to go into synchro monsters like Yazi, or summon and destroy Zefraniu letting you search counter traps to stop your opponent. When Destroyed Yazi lets you special summon Mare Mare preferably. Mare Mare then creates three tokens to use to make Linkuriboh and Link Spider to then go into a 4 monster Skull Dread. Use your best judgment from that point. It's not the best deck but I have fun using it and I hope you do as well.

deck_excerpt: ABC Card of Demise Stun Control (Going First)
deck_description: I've been playing around with ABC a bit this past 2 weeks and I've come up with a really good ABC Card of Demise build that is consistent and allows you to stun your opponent and win by continuously beating down your opponent every turn with ABC-Dragon Buster. I've made this deck as consistent as possible, and after making it from scratch and making its brick rate low, it can now easily stand up to the tier 1 decks of this format. The goal of the deck is to go first, set a bunch of traps like There Can Be Only One and hopefully discard the rest of your hand off Card of Demise. You want to have as many ABC pieces in your hand as possible turn 1 after using Card of Demise this way you can discard those ABC pieces for next turn when you'll be able to summon Dragon Buster. I also added a really spicy tech I've known about for years but never really found the deck to use it in, Dragon Ice. I really like this card, especially in this deck because going second, you can discard an ABC piece from your hand to special summon this dragon that can be used as link material on your following turn. Another card I decided to put in that I really like is Electromagnetic Turtle. When playing on ygopro, this card has saved me from dying so many times and has given me that extra turn I need to turn the game state around in my favor. I think it is really helpful if you use it at the right time since its effect is only once per duel. Dragon Ice has also saved me many times too, since its special summon effect can also be used while its in the graveyard. Overall, I really like this deck, it is a lot of fun to play and I had a great time playing it on ygopro with everyone. Stick around for more!

deck_excerpt: Two of my favorite meta archetypes combined into an ultra powerhouse!
deck_description: This is my favorite "go-second" deck because it contains two of my favorite meta archetypes: Mekk-Knights and Crusadias. They have great synergy since they both can special summon from the hand, which brings a spicy card known as "Pinpoint Landing", which lets you draw a card when you special summon from the hand, but only once that turn. The spiciest card in this deck, in my opinion, is "Super Team Buddy Force Unite!", which lets you special summon a monster with a different name, but has the same original type. For example, if you control a Maximus or any Mekk-Knight, you can special summon ANY psychic monster from the deck. Don't fear of that card getting destroyed, because it can set another copy from the deck if it is destroyed! Hope that you enjoy one of my favorite meta decks :). Comment down on what I can do to make this deck better. Thanks!
